is essentially the same as rent collection explains a report from grassroots leadership ccas chief executive damon t hininger said the good news about this is that we are going to be able to enjoy a full year of tax savings for  in the first quarter of  the firm realized a  million income tax benefit related to the companys recent conversion into a reit grassroots leadership notes that at a time of drastic budget cuts throughout the public sector cca expects to make  million savings in tax payments for  due to its reit status cca had tried an reit in the past with disastrous results as prison legal news explains cca formed prison realty trust and a separate operating company but due to various factors including poor management decisions the reit defaulted on its debt and the companys stock dropped to under  a share putting it at risk of being delisted from the new york stock exchange cca subsequently reversed its reit conversion and faced shareholder lawsuits that alleged various corporate officers and directors had concealed information and made false and misleading statements the suits were eventually settled for approximately  million in stock and cash separately in new mexico in  cca sought a tax exemption from state city and local governments for payments it receives from the federal government for federal inmates held in facilities inside new mexico cca eventually negotiated an exemption only from state taxes while agreeing to taxes on the local level states end relationships with cca kentucky kentucky had housed prisoners in private prisons for approximately  years including three ccarun facilities but decided not to renew its last contract with cca in  hawaii after two lawsuits for inmate deaths and allegations of prisoner abuse hawaii stated its intention to bring prisoners back to the islands but in  the state signed a new threeyear deal with cca in arizona however the contract was signed as governor neil abercrombies administration was reportedly making p