en texas corecivic formerly the corrections corporation of america cca is a company that owns and manages private prisons and detention centers and operates others on a concession basis cofounded in nashville tennessee by thomas w beasley chairman of the state republican party doctor robert crants and t don hutto in  it received initial investments from jack c massey the founder of hospital corporation of america vanderbilt university and the tennessee valley authority as of  the company is the largest private corrections company in the united states it manages more than  state and federal correctional and detention facilities with a capacity of more than  beds in  states and the district of columbia the company’s revenue in  exceeded  billion by  its contracts with federal correctional and detention authorities generated up to  of its revenues it operated  federal facilities with the capacity for  prisoners by  corrections corporation of america cca along with geo group were running more than  prisons and detention centres ccas revenues in  were bn controversies related to the company include poor treatment of inmates and disclosure of oversight lobbying efforts to conceal details of operations a lawsuit about gang influence at an idaho facility and substantial falsification of records to hide understaffing cooperation with local law enforcement in a school drug sweep and the deadly  riot at a mississippi facility contents  history  overview  inmate rehabilitation  occupancy and profitability  employment issues  ownership  immigrant detention facilities  incidents protests and investigations  t don hutto residential center  eloy detention center  central detention center of arizona  south texas residential center dilley texas  laredo processing center  houston processing center  closed facilities  colorado  kentucky  minnesota  oklahoma  controversies  treatment of inmates and disclosure of shortcomings of oversight  lobbying efforts  lawsuit about gang influence i